The time has come to demolish our bedroom. The last room in the house where nothing was done, just a bit of decoration.
Remove the ugly electric fireplace and the hearth. Frame the chimney, replace the damaged plaster and sand it. Make a custom closet.
We always start with a quick pencil sketch...
The messy step is finished.
I found several dead birds at the back of the flue; all dried out :(
Ready for plastering next week
Excited about the little nook on the side
Insert the new closet here (it's not like we've already started drawing it 🙈)
Oh, look at what we found behind the radiator!
And we even thought to add a charming little air vent to prevent the chimney from taking in moisture
The chimney sweep took care of installing the cap and the wind deflector. It should be a bit safer for the crows that nest up there 🪺
The plasterer is done. We'll install the floor tomorrow!
The cork underlayer is in place, I improvised a wood dust extractor using a toilet paper roll as an accessory for the vacuum cleaner 😂
Some of the boards have been sorted and are ready to be placed. We're just taking a tea break
Well, progress has been slow today due to extremely delicate cuts around the door frames to achieve a smooth transition to the corridor (which is also being installed). @user45@twitter.com has been cursing me
Done, but on roller skates! Finishing touch: the incomprehensible instructions for putting together the new bed. We'll sleep well tonight!
Left to do is the hallway floor and all the baseboards. The decorator comes in a month, so for now, at home, it's chic plaster without any finishing touches
A little evening DIY session to remove the lower sections of the door frames with a tenon saw/handsaw where we want the floor to fit perfectly.
The hallway's cork underlayer has also been installed
We finished the hallway floor yesterday! Then off at 5 AM this morning to pick up Thing 1 from Heathrow, then nap and last stretch for the hallway; baseboards put in place. We'll take care of the sealing when the glue takes.
